<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36071f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36071f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36071f"> 71(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> composing draught / fed on the bottle</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Hospital Nurse deposed when examined on oath by the Committee that a medicine called significantly &ldquo;The Bottle&rdquo; was handed round to them all at intervals indiscriminately. She did not know what was in it, but supposed it was a &ldquo;<mark>composing draught</mark>&rdquo;, for &ldquo;the children were easy for an hour or two after taking it.&rdquo; Consigned to the den above described, and <mark>fed on bread and water and &ldquo;The Bottle&rdquo;</mark>, they soon died. <small> James Collins, <a name="JCLO" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#JCLO"><cite title="source">Life in Old Dublin</cite></a> (l913) 103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
